                              @{u}A Word From Pete@{uu}

In early December 1999, @{BG fill}@{"Bedlam BBS" Link BedlamBBS}@{BG background} vanished in the blink of an eye, gone
were 34,400 Files, gone was a Userbase of 498, and lastly, gone was 3 years
of a hobby I really loved doing.  OK I thought, it was good while it lasted,
but what's gone is gone there is plenty of other things I can do, play Games
on the PC which I got from a mate, and even spend a Christmas doing things
normal people do, eat, drink, watch the television and not have to make sure
that there were new Files online for those people who call over the Festive
Season.

So, over the next four or five weeks I tried to get on with other things,
but there is so much you can take moving little men around and killing
aliens in UFO: Terror From The Deep.  Then I got the first pangs of BBS
withdrawal symptoms, so let's try to start up a BBS on the PC I thought,
but found the Software not as User friendly as MAX's, and out of the
corner of my eye, I could see my burnt out AMIGA, with its trashed mother-
board and buggered Hard-Drive.

With the help from my mate, we built up the AMIGA again with bits and bobs
he begged from others, and we got it working again.  So, with a borrowed
1GB Hard-Drive, I started to re-create @{BG fill}@{"Bedlam BBS" Link BedlamBBS}@{BG background} on the AMIGA, but even
then I was unsure if I was doing the right thing.  2 months is a long time
to be offline, Users of BBSes don't hang around, they move on to pastures
new, but I went ahead regardless and things got better when my mate swapped
the electrics of my 4.3GB Hard-Drive with one of his old ones, and now I had
it all back, my AMIGA, my Hard-Drive and finally put @{BG fill}@{"Bedlam BBS" Link BedlamBBS}@{BG background} back online
with a very small Filebase and a fingers-crossed SysOp.

So, to all those people who used to call @{BG fill}@{"Bedlam BBS" Link BedlamBBS}@{BG background}, it's now back and on
it's way once again, so give us a call on 0116-278-7773 24hrs ;)

Finally I would like to thank the following people for there valued help in
getting me started up again:-

Dunkie (SysOp Of @{BG fill}@{"Quest BBS" Link QuestBBS}@{BG background}) who was Chief Beta Tester for @{BG fill}@{"Bedlam BBS" Link BedlamBBS}@{BG background}.
Ninja (SysOp Of @{BG fill}@{"Arachnoids BBS" Link ArachnoidsBBS}@{BG background}) for sorting out my Hard-Drive.
S.N.S (SysOp Of @{BG fill}@{"Skull Monkey BBS" Link SkullMonkeyBBS}@{BG background}) for his help with the AREXX Scripts.
My mate Neil for resurrecting and rebuilding my AMIGA A1200 :)))

And lastly, I'd like to thank the 16 Users who called @{BG fill}@{"Bedlam BBS" Link BedlamBBS}@{BG background} in the
first week of its relaunch...many thanks for the Files lads, keep'em
coming!!!

It's good to be back :)

See you Next Issue...

