  @{u}MAXS BBS Door Programming Tutorial: Part 3 - By Trevor Rycraft 'Kryten'@{uu}

                @{b}VERY SIMPLE PAGER (Does Not Call Chat Flag)@{ub}

This Tutorial is intended for AMOSPro Programmers who want to learn MAXS BBS
Door Coding and requires AMOSPRO 2+ and KewlDoors.library by Niki Murkett
(Available from AMINET).  Sorry...absolute beginners should consult The AMOS
Manual.

' [Setup the ESC+[ variable (used for colour changes etc..)] 
ESC$=Chr$(27)+"["

' [LETS OPEN THE MAXS PORT GETTING THE PORT NUMBER FROM MAXS ITSELF] 
C$=Command Line$ : NOD$=Right$(C$,1) : If -1=Kd Open Port(Val(NOD$)) Then End 

' [Get the user name]
NAME$=Kd User Name$

' [Need i say more?] 
NULL=Kd Clear Screen

' [Position the cursor]
NULL=Kd Locate(1,1)

' [Change cursor colour] 
NULL=Kd Print(ESC$+"0m")

' [Ask the user what they want to page for (max 60 chars long)]
IN$=Kd Input$("Reason To Page : ",60)
NULL=Kd Clear Screen

' [LeTs PaGe!] 
NULL=Kd Locate(1,2)
NULL=Kd Print(NAME$+" is paging!")
NULL=Kd Locate(1,3)
NULL=Kd Print("REASON: "+IN$)
NULL=Kd Locate(1,5)
NULL=Kd Print("[               ]")
NULL=Kd Print(ESC$+"47;31m") : Rem [WHITE BACKGROUND RED PEN] 
NULL=Kd Locate(2,5)

' [Begining of loop] 

For LUPE=1 To 15
' [Check for the sysop pressing the key as many times as we can]   
' [Not very efficient but works for this example =)] 

If Kd Get Special Key<>0 Then Goto ANSWER
NULL=Kd Print(Chr$(7)) : Rem [MAKE THE SCREEN BLEEP/FLASH ON BBS SIDE]

If Kd Get Special Key<>0 Then Goto ANSWER
' [Print a dot (with colours as above)]
