   - Messages addressed to certain names can be bounced, remapped, or acted
     upon by a program or script which is launched as soon as a message
     with that name is imported.  Optionally protect these with passwords 
     provided in the subject line, like an AreaFix robot.

- Fully functional news and email gating system
   - Zeus features superlative gating abilities

Zeus takes the Internet and makes it a part of your BBS.  E-Mail and
Newsgroups can be taken and completely transparently integrated with your
BBS.  While other BBS packages might be flooding FidoNet with messages
addressed to "ALL", Zeus reverses the trend and can take Internet messages
and put the correct To: name in them!  This is unique to Zeus in the whole
BBS World!

   - Dupe detection
   - Reply linking
   - Message Bouncing
   - Extremely quick index format

All features provided by Zeus' gateway program, ZGate, which is so
integrated with Zeus the distinction of a gateway is lost.  This program
allows all your downlinks (or rather, those you give access to) to also use
your Internet gate, giving them (your points, or other nodes) E-Mail
addresses, access to mailing lists, newsgroups, whatever you want to
provide.

   - Support for Dynamic IP Internet accounts

You don't need a static Internet account, but it helps.

   - Map To: fields, give newsgroups and mailing list messages To: names!
   - Map the user name before the @ sign to whatever you want for each
     user, or leave each user with the default Internet addresses of their
     name and alias.
   - AMINET mirroring to your file base!

Take all or part of the new files uploaded to AMINET.  The intelligent
'mirroring' program replaces older versions of archives on your BBS and
takes down the directories of AMINET you choose, perhaps if you wish also
limiting the size of files which will be downloaded.

- Unlimited number of message areas
   - Fields include for each message area -
      - Low and High Accesses,
      - Gender required to access area
      - Minimum age to access area
      - Usenet moderated group follow-up base

Configure access to areas individually, as well as being able to define for
each User individually and also through templates (described later).

   - Message Base type
      - Local
      - Echomail
      - Netmail
      - UUCP
      - UUCP Mail

An area can act differently depending on its type.

   - Message Base Storage type
      - Standard Zeus format
      - StarMsg (#.msg) format
      - NNTP network format
      - Tin format
      - Elm Mail format

As described above when we talked about the Message Base libraries.

   - Flags -
      - Private Base
        (All Messages are automatically made Private)
      - Aliases (Aliases are then used by default)
      - Hi-ASCII Stripping
      - Allow Users to Delete Own Written Messages
      - Allowing Quoting in Base or not
      - And more!

As well as areas acting differently depending on their type, you can set
flags for each area which can control certain vital parts of their
operation.

   - Processor for each written message allowing -
      - Jive, Kraut & Valley Girl (amongst others) message translators!
      - Anything plug-in you want to modify written messages

This fabulous feature lets you define a program which is run on messages
posted to certain areas (the 'executable processor' can be assigned to one
or more areas easily).  Imagine a user posting to an area in English, but
as soon as they save the message it is translated to French by an
automatic script!  This is possible!

- Unlimited number of External Message Editors
   - Line Editor supplied
   - Full Screen Editor supplied
   - Local Users may use Local Editors (e.g. CygnusEd, GoldEd)

SysOps may use the text editor they are most comfortable with.  No more
struggling with those terrible line editors, when you can use GoldEd!

- Waiting Mail support

Waiting mail for each User is stored in a quick access index, ensuring that
Zeus never needs to scan the whole message base to look for new messages
addressed to a User (unlike some BBS packages!).  Zeus can store millions of
messages easily, so it is important that messages for a User are found
quickly and easily.  A User of a Zeus BBS can also 'unsubscribe' an area,
meaning that they will not be notified of personal messages in that area
again, although they can go back and read them if they wish.

- Forward and Reverse Reply Linking

Follow threads easily.  Zeus can also group messages by subject!

- Anonymous Sender and Recipient Fields
- Message Display system -
   - Configurable Coloured Quote lines
   - Configurable Coloured or Hideable Kludges, Seen-Bys, Paths
   - Supports *emphasis* /like/ #this#!

Ever been bored staring at a very plain display while reading messages?  No
more!  Not only can Zeus colour specific parts of messages, like the quoted
lines, it also supports the standard *bold* /italic/ and _underline_
emphasis markers, as well as some #more# special ones.

- Message Signature Support

Users can add signatures to messages, and not only that, they can have a
different signature for each network or Special Interest Group ("SIG", see
later!).

- Message Searching System by -
   - Sub-string within Text,
   - Exact or Sub-string within From, To and Subject fields

A complete break away from what you'd expect from a normal BBS, Zeus can
even search for messages based on the parameters you give!

- Stored High Pointers for each User
- Fully Intuition-Based GUI Configuration Utilities for every
  aspect of the powerful Message Configurations
   - Message Area Editor
   - Message Display Colour Editor
   - Network Configuration
      - FidoNet Addressing
      - FidoNet Export/Import Systems
      - FidoNet Netmail Routing
   - Message/File/Signature Editor Configuration Program
- Graphical Display of Current Message Statistics (include High,
  Low and High Sent By Net pointers)
- Full Logging to Screen and Disk
- QWK/Bluewave offline packer system

Yes, of course - Zeus has a QWK and Bluewave (combined) offline packer
system.  It also support text formats for offline reading like MBBS.

@{u}The File Sub-System@{uu}

The file system is controlled by file base libraries, just like the message
base libraries.  Only one is available at present, but this offers fast
access times and a fully Chrono/Alpha indexed file system.

@{u}File Specifications@{uu}

- Unlimited number of file areas
   - Fields include -
      - Low and High Accesses required
      - Minimum BPS rate to download and upload
      - The Minimum Age required
      - Files require validation
      - And more!

Like message areas, each file area can be set individually, per user or via
Templates.

   - Areas can be made to use 8.3 MS-DOS filenames only

An excellent feature for PC file areas, this restricts file names to
xxxxxxxx.xxx format - for the MS-DOS system.  Even if someone tries to
upload a longer filename, Zeus will intelligently cut it down to 8.3 size!

- Multiple Area Path Support
   - Each area can be extended transparently over as many
     hard disks, CD-ROMs, or even network connections you have.

I cannot emphasise how important a feature this can be.  The Multi-Paths (as
they are known) allow you to do such magic as having /each/ /area/ of your
file base over several hard disks and CD-ROMs, and as each hard disk fills
up Zeus automatically (with no outside intervention) starts using a hard
disk with enough space on.  In this way, you can extend your file base over
many disks completely transparently, and very easily.  Another thought:
while the AMIGA OS 3.5 and better support partitions larger than 4GB, some
older programs do not.  What if you have more than 4GB of files?  Zeus will
let you essentially treat two or more file partitions as one, so problem
solved!

- Transfer Sub-System
   - Supports the HYDRA bi-directional file transfer and chat
     mode protocol.
   - Supports enhanced XPR 2.001 libraries such as Dmodem
   - Supports standard XPR libraries, including -
      - Zmodem Batch
      - Zmodem-8k
      - ZedZap
      - Ymodem
      - Xmodem
      - and most others you can find!
   - Supports external transfer programs such as SModem too!
   - Files can be checked for duplication before upload
   - File Report Statistics can easily be obtained through Rexx

A powerful, standard file transfer system.

- Number of files limited only by disk-space
- Index files work equally well with a large or small file base
- Very fast scanning system

Zeus' indexed file base ensures that no matter how many files you have,
they can be found on disk in a fraction of a second.  No waiting while the
BBS slowly looks through each record one by one.

- Scans can be based upon -
   - Chronology
   - Alphabetically
   - Globally
   - By Date order
- All Scans can be performed both forwards and backwards
- Very quick index base format which protects against disk
  fragmentation by storing the file descriptions in just a few,
  sorted indexes
- CD-ROM/Slow Device pre-copy supported
- Signal access means that multidisk-disk CD-ROM players are
  never left changing back and forth over disks, but copy a file
  at a time
- Each file has a unique index number for quick retrieval
- Rebuild/Optimise Utility supplied to keep index files trimmed
  and working efficiently
- Informative File Structure includes -
   - Index Number
   - File Name
   - File Size
   - Upload Date
   - Last Download Date
   - Number Of Downloads file has had
   - Name of User who Uploaded the file
- Flags include
   - Unvalidated File
   - Free File (no impact on credit ratios)
   - Temporarily deleted file
   - Off-line file: for when access to the disk that holds is
     unavailable (think CD-ROM!)
   - and more!
- File Description can be of unlimited length, to include all
  relevant information about each file

Notably, file descriptions are not limited as in other BBS packages.  You
may choose to limit them yourself as SysOp, of you may decide that 44
characters across and 6 lines down isn't enough.

- Users may insert their own comments about each file
- New Uploaded files, through Rexx, can be
   - Checked for viruses with almost any virus checker available
   - Stripped of BBS adverts
   - Stripped of unwanted files
   - and BBS adverts may be added to archive
- Marking Files
   - Unlimited number of marked files, or limited by the SysOp
     to stop users marking the whole file base
   - Marked files can be added in ranges such as '#-#',
     '#,#,#-#'
   - AMIGA DOS wildcards supported when marking files
     'ZEUS#?.?HA'
   - User can delete, using ranges, currently marked files
- Credit System
   - File Ratio
   - Byte Ratio
   - Max Bytes per Day
   - Max Files per Day
   - Free Files allowed before first Upload
   - Free Bytes allowed before first Download
- All Credits can be disabled
- In-built File lister Program, totally configurable, or brew your own
  based on our examples with just three main commands!
- Powerful GUI File Editor program
   - Allows powerful Adding, and Bulk Uploading of files
   - GUI Editing of currently on-line files
   - Links to your favourite Local Editor to edit file
     descriptions
   - Allows easy and powerful perusal of your file bases
- Fully Intuition-Based GUI Configuration Utilities for every
  aspect of the powerful File Configurations
   - File Area Editor
   - General File Configuration Editor
   - XPR/Transfer Protocol Editor

@{u}Integrated Features@{uu}

Some of the more powerful features of Zeus interact with the File, Msg
and Main BBS Server.

- A Powerful User Template System.  Each Template can be attached
  to a different access level, and set to the default settings by
  the GUI User Editor.  However, each User may have different
  template accesses to the defaults, and these can be changed by
  the User Editor
   - Each Template can specify -
      - Max Calls Per Day
      - Max Minutes Per Call
      - Max Minutes Per Day
      - File Ratio
      - Byte Ratio
      - Max Bytes Per Day
      - Max Files Per Day
      - Free Files
      - Free Bytes
      - Max Written Messages Per Day
    - Each File Area can have different Access Bits set -
      - Access File Area
      - View Files in Area
      - Download Files in Area
      - Upload Files in Area
      - Edit Files Uploaded by User in Area
      - Edit any File in Area
      - Access Unvalidated Files in Area
      - Validate any Files in Area
      - Delete any File in Area
      - SysOp access in Area
   - Each Message Area can have different Access Bits set -
      - Access Message Area
      - Read Messages in Area
      - Write Messages in Area
      - Write Private Messages in Area
      - Read Private Messages in Area
      - Kill Messages Written by User in Area
      - Kill any Messages in Area
      - Attach Files to Messages in Area
      - Send Crash Netmails in Area
      - SysOp access in Area

- Message and file areas to be added into Special Interest Groups,
  to divide large BBSes into manageable pieces
   - Unlimited Number of SIGS
   - Low and High Access levels to SIGs can defined

- Archiver System.  For use with uploaded files, viewing files and
  unpacking mail, archivers are configured in a GUI Configuration
  program for universal use of which ever archive formats you wish
  to support
   - Recognition strings - Allow archive types to be detected
     without the use of a three letter postfix
   - Pack, unpack and test strings
   - Support for most known archivers, even encoders such as
     uuencode can be defined
   - Archivers can be set as 'internal use only' so users can't
     use them to, for example, pack mail for offline reading.
   - External tools to use Zeus's archiver system in other programs.

@{u}Conversion@{uu}

Zeus is currently supplied with utilities to convert essential data files
from other major Bulletin Board packages.

  - Xenolink 1.97

      - File Area Data Conversion Utility
      - Message Area Data Conversion Utility
      - User Conversion Utility (requires .password file in USER:
        directories)

  - DLG 1.0

      - File Area Data Conversion Utility
      - Message Area Data Conversion Utility
      - User File Data Conversion.
      - .fd file description Conversion Utility.

  - TransAmiga

      - File Area Data Conversion Utility
      - Message Area Data Conversion Utility

  - Excelsior 1.12j

      - Rudimentary File Area Data Conversion Utility
      - Rudimentary Msg Area Data Conversion Utility

  - CNET

      - User File Data Conversion.

A MAX's BBS User converter is currently under construction.

@{u}Doors@{uu}

- Zeus supports many different door emulation libraries.

  - Paragon Door support.
  - DLG Door support via an emulation library.
  - Xenolink Door support via an emulation library.
  - MAX's BBS.
  - AmiExpress (/X) doors which do not rely on fixed /X data files.

- ABBEREXX Door Support.
  This system also includes support for:

  - CNet Rexx
  - XenoLink Rexx

- Full CLI Door support.

  - Configurable CTRL-C/D breaking commands.
  - Support for all standard AMIGA DOS packets, allowing all Shell/stdio
    doors to work well with Zeus.
  - Integrate anything usable from the Shell/CLI, not just doors!

- Full Shell Access with command line history.

  - Enables complete remote SysOping without needing a seperate 'getty'
    system.

- Zeus doors! Very fast internal door format, taking full advantage of the
  features provided by Zeus.

- Zeus ARexx doors.  Based on our ScriptSet mechanism, you can use doors
  written for the Zeus ARexx command set.  ARexx doors once got a 'bad
  press', but this we can guarantee is due to inferior ARexx ports in other
  systems!

@{u}Zeus Asyncronous Packet Protocol@{uu}

*ZAPP*

Eh? Whats that then?

It's the future of BBSes that's what it is!  You won't find it in any other
more feeble BBS Software and it's damned exciting stuff.  All you need do is
log onto the BBS as per normal using a provided Zapp.device.  When you
arrive all is as normal.  So what's the fuss all about?

Quick flick onto Workbench reveals, an Icon, yes an Icon.  You gently caress
your mouse button and open the icon.  Inside, lying like an opened clam is
the BBS File area.  Drag and Drop, Transfer via DOpus, yes it's all there.
Confused, I bet you are.  So you copy a file in DOpus, like a 5 MB
Animation.  So what do you do now then.  On more feeble software you go an
have your tea that's what you do.

So you idly flick back to the TERM or NCOMM screen to watch the transfer
window telling you theres another 20 mins of transfer to go.  Eh?  There's
no transfer screen.  You click a key, the BBS responds!  You click another
and enter the games menu.  Who turned that radio on, you shout to your
girlfriend?  Hang on a minute, the sound came from your speakers.  No, it's
the Jack Daniels taking effect.  Surely not?  You press another key, another
sound comes from your speakers.  It's Bugs Bunny saying 'Whats Up Doc'.

Brain is going into overload, you now have a new Device on WB and aural
stimulii coming through your speakers.  This cannot be happening.  It can't
be true?

Your girlfriend wanders in the room.  She is semi-naked and gives you that
look.  She wanders away into your bedroom and you know what she wants.
Stuff that you think, I can do that tomorrow!  She slams the door, never
mind.

Warily you start a game of Hyper Typer.  The game commences and so you
check the modem lights.  The file transfer is still happening.  You flick
back to Workbench and suddenly a window appears.  'Hi There' is the title.
'Good Stuff This' is the body of the message.  'For Sure' is the name of the
button you have to press to make it go away.  Help!  Whats happening?

You have entered the world of Zapp.  You have experienced the future and
salvation of BBSes as we know them.

ZAPP also means you can serve HTML webpages from your BBS, and, soon, full
Internet access.

ZAPP is a fully featured packet networking system, which like all Zeus
features can be written for and expanded by any programmer through our
public APIs.

@{u}Developer Information@{uu}

While Zeus is fully programmable and totally configurable through ARexx,
we also supply just as much power to programmers who wish to use compiled
and assembled programming languages.

Zeus is supplied with many files to help developers.  We have two main Zeus
support libraries with over 230 BBS functions accessible for programmers.

Full autodocs are included to help developers create tools for Zeus.

Every aspect of the BBS can be controlled through these support libraries,
including full message and file base manipulation.

@{u}But There's More!!!@{uu}

The most important aspect of Zeus' operational abilities have not yet been
explored.  We have stated earlier that Zeus can emulate any BBS package, or
take any form you wish.

This is accomplished through the ARexx scripting system.

Here is an example main menu in Zeus:

/*
** MainMenu.zeus -- The main menu.
*/

Options Results
Parse Arg Line

ChkCarrier
if RC ~= 0 then exit

MenuLoop:
   Signal on syntax

   SetStatus '"At Main Menu"'

   Display 'Main/MainMenu' IsMenu

   ShowEvents

   do forever
      Write '"\n`[0m`[32m`[1;37m boebingo main menu `[35m[%1%02ld|:%2%02ld|]`[37m :"'
      Read IsMenu
      if RC ~= 0 then Exit
      CmdString = RESULT

      Cmd = 'Signal Option_'CmdString
      Interpret Cmd
      end

/* This is the main meat of the menu. This controls the I/O from the
   BBS to the user, and prompts for a keypress */

Option_?:
   GetUserFlag 'Expert'
   if RC = 1 then Display 'Main/MainMenu'
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_E:
   CallScript 'Options/EditOptions.pl'
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_U:
   SetStatus '"Listing users"'

   ZDoor '"UserList 'Line'"'
   WaitReturn
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_P:
   SetStatus '"Paging SysOp ..."'
   ZDoor '"ChatPage/ChatPage 'Line'"'
   if RC == 1 then do
      ChangeMsgArea 1
      Write '"\f\n`[32mLeaving feedback to SysOp ...\n"'
      FlushInput
      PushInput '"Nick Loman\n\r"'
      PushInput '"ChatPage Message"'
      CallScript 'Msg/WriteMsg'
   end
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_L:
   SetStatus '"Leaving feedback to SysOp"'

   RIPReset
   ChangeMsgArea 1
   Write '"\n`[32mLeaving feedback to SysOp\n"'
   FlushInput
   PushInput '"Nick Loman\n\r"'
   CallScript 'Msg/WriteMsg'
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_W:
   RIPReset
   CallScript 'Main/WhosOnline'
   WaitReturn
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_N:
   RIPReset
   CallScript 'Main/WhosOnline'
   CallScript 'Main/SendNodeMsg'
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_T:
   Signal MenuLoop

Option_M:
   NextScript 'Msg/MsgMenu'
   Exit

Option_F:
   NextScript 'File/FileMenu'
   Exit

Option_O:
   NextScript 'Doors/DoorMenu'
   Exit

Option_B:
   NextScript 'Bltns/BltnMenu'
   Exit

Option_C:
   ZDoor '"XlkDoor 'Line' ChatPage/ChatPage"'
   Signal Menuloop

Option_Z:
   NextScript 'Zeus/Zeus'
   Exit

syntax:
   GetGlobalCmd '"'CmdString'"'
   if RC = 0 then Interpret RESULT
   Signal MenuLoop

Even if you are not an ARexx guru, I am sure you will appreciate the wide-
ranging possibilities for your BBS with such a flexible system.  Even if you
have not the slightest clue as to what to do with ARexx, don't fret - the
Zeus team are willing to do the work to write your menus for you, when they
have time - how's that for commitment?

@{u}End Words@{uu}

Thanks for reading this far!  I'm sorry it went on for over six thousand
words, but I am still as enthusiastic about Zeus as I was years ago, more
so even!

Perhaps you'd like more information on Zeus now?  You can get more by
downloading the ZeusInfo4.lha information pack from the Zeus Developments
