                           Why the long ringing?
                           ---------------------

The first time you ring, YOU switch on the power supply to my Computer! ;-)
The 60 second hang up, means you are waiting for my Computer to load the 
Host Software.  The 2nd time you Call, the Host Software will be loaded,
waiting for a Call, and you will get through.  Please note that my Computer
is fully disconnected from the mains power supply when you first Call, so no
matter for how long you ring, or how intermittent your ringing is, you will
not get through to this Computer until it has loaded it's operating system,
and then loaded the Host Software ready for a Call.

Naturally, when you log off this system, you switch off the power supply to
my Computer and it waits for another Call.  My Computer is controlled by a
Card of my own design and build (see more about it on the BBS).  Download
from the Public Download Menu a file called DESCATOC.DOC, there is a full
colour picture of the prototype Card in this file, as well as extensive
info on the Card itself.  The Card has many unique features, even holds
power if another Call incoming within 10 minutes of last Call!  See it for
yourself.
